    "Eggshell powder (ESP) results in moderate reductions in workability, while (WGP) impacts fluidity based on the fineness and quantity of the glass particles used. 2.",
    "SCMs like SF, MK, and GGBFS significantly boost compressive and flexural strength, especially when used at optimal replacement rates of 10-30%.",
    "FA contributes to long-term strength gains, particularly after 28 days of curing.",
    "POFA and RHA enhance compressive strength at moderate replacement rates, though excessive use may weaken strength.Other SCMs, such as zeolite, ESP, and SCBA, show varied results, with strength improvements at lower doses but possible declines at higher levels. 3.",
    "Many SCMs improve concrete durability by reducing permeability to chloride ions, enhancing resistance to sulfate attack, and lowering water absorption."
